Entry 1441190-496:

Neural Stunner

A wepon developed by Vortual Inc, a company based on Vorticon VI. The neural stunner uses a telentric generator to generate telentromagnetic radiation which is then passed through a telentopic crystal to convert it to variable frequency. At low frequency the radiation will cause little more than a feeling of disorientation, but at higher frequencies it results in paralysis, deah and even physical disintergration. The peace loving vorticons origionally intended this as a means of quickly frying potato crisps, but it appears to have been adopted for more violent purposes, such as popping popcorn.

See also, Commander Keen, Tuberia, Potato CrispsA proud member of the signature stealing society

title: Re: Vortican IV:
content:
I know nothing of Droidiccus Prime, so I cannot judge it. As for the others:

Mars is cold and lacking in atmosphere. Also, life is lacking in variety.

Vorticon IV is lovely, but possibly a little too like Earth in terms of civilization.

Gnosticus IV was a close second for its astonishing variety of life and environs to explore. But it seems to be lacking in tourist infrastructure.

Korath III is crazy-looking from space. If there was more to see there then I might go there.

I chose Fribbulus Xax because it has the kind of wierd environment and alien species combined with the technological-ness that I like. As for teh problem of the unfriendly aliens, all I really fear are the giks. Those things have gotten the better of me SO many times...!
